  "description": "¶Dependent function types (Pi-types) In Agda, every function type can be dependent. The syntax:\nf : (x : A) → B x declares a function where the return type B x depends on the input value x. When the return type does not depend on the input, this reduces to the ordinary function type A → B.\nExample. A function that returns a type based on a boolean:\nT : Bool → Set T true = Nat T false = String A function using this:\n",
